---
name: scljet-sql-aggregate
description: SclJet SQL aggregates — COUNT / SUM / MIN / MAX over a (filtered) table (matches reference sqlite3)
backends: [int, js]
---

# SclJet SQL aggregates

`SELECT COUNT(*|col), SUM(col), MIN(col), MAX(col), AVG(col), TOTAL(col) FROM t [WHERE …]`
computes the aggregate(s) over the WHERE-filtered rows and returns one row. Every result is
byte-identical to reference sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file (verified
out-of-band); locked here across backends. Reals render like the sqlite3 CLI (integer-valued
reals keep a trailing `.0`).

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def run(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "t", "CREATE TABLE t(id INTEGER, name TEXT, age INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("carol"), SqlInteger(31L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("alice"), SqlInteger(27L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("dave"), SqlInteger(45L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("bob"), SqlInteger(29L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    run(db, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM t")
    run(db, "SELECT COUNT(*), SUM(age), MIN(age), MAX(age) FROM t")
    run(db, "SELECT SUM(age) FROM t WHERE age > 28")
    run(db, "SELECT MIN(name), MAX(name) FROM t")
    run(db, "SELECT COUNT(age) FROM t WHERE name >= 'bob'")
    run(db, "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM t WHERE age > 100")
    run(db, "SELECT MAX(age) FROM t WHERE age > 100")
    run(db, "SELECT AVG(age), TOTAL(age) FROM t")
    run(db, "SELECT AVG(age) FROM t WHERE age > 28")
    run(db, "SELECT TOTAL(age) FROM t WHERE age > 100")
```
